        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1745148615" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10574237610599289904">As the title implies, Sodom and Gomorra is the descent into hell - or more aptly, the cruel and unseemly underside of the society described by Le Coté de Guermantes. We have the craven Charlus and Jupien (mirroring the lesbian scene that the narrator sees in the first book). The narrator has his first taste of death and mourning as his grandmother which cuts him to the bone. It is an exciting and brutal book full of action and description in equal parts and the growing obsession of the narrator </span>
  <span id="freeText10574237610599289904" style="display:none">As the title implies, Sodom and Gomorra is the descent into hell - or more aptly, the cruel and unseemly underside of the society described by Le Coté de Guermantes. We have the craven Charlus and Jupien (mirroring the lesbian scene that the narrator sees in the first book). The narrator has his first taste of death and mourning as his grandmother which cuts him to the bone. It is an exciting and brutal book full of action and description in equal parts and the growing obsession of the narrator for the possession of Albertine. This of course is the subject of the next book. Le Prisonniere.... </span>
